The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, September 13, 2003 				 My Best Friends Wedding
																								Its Sameer Vermas best friend Avinash Advanis wedding day  the day everyone has been waiting for  the beautiful bride Ayesha Singh, her over-emotional mother Jaspreet, her control freak father Daler and a host of friends, well-wishers and family. While everyone, including the hotel staff, and vivacious housekeeper Reena, is busy ensuring that the ceremony goes off as planned, the groom is busy trying to hide a beautiful girl, Reema, in his hotel room. He found her sleeping next to him, in his bed, on his wedding day, in his honeymoon suite and Avinash cant remember how she landed up in his bed! Meanwhile, the baraat land up and poor Avinash has no clue about his next move. In steps his friend Sameer, who reluctantly agrees to declare Reena as his new girlfriend from Delhi. But this complicates the problem further as Sameers actual girlfriend is also expected at the wedding! Directed and enacted by Sundeep Sikand, the play also stars VJ Kim Jagtiani, Shivani Tanksale, Zarine Farooq and Nisha Sareenth. Hosted by Showhouse, this play is being staged in the city as part of McDowell Signature Theatre Festival.																								When: Today at 6.30 pm and tomorrow at 3.30 pm amp; 6.30 pm																								Where: G.D. Birla Sabhagar
